               SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  1.1  "Defensive Grid Labs" or "the Proprietor" shall refer
       to the founding organization known as Defensive Grid
       Labs, its principals, authorized maintainers, legal
       representatives, successors, and assigns.

  1.2  "the Software" shall refer to all source code, object
       code, compiled binaries, documentation, configuration
       files, build scripts, assets, visual media, and all
       other tangible or intangible materials contained in,
       associated with, or distributed alongside the
       repository located at:
       https://github.com/DwijeshG/Grid-Guardian,
       including all past, present, and future versions,
       revisions, and releases thereof.

  1.3  "Derivative Work" shall mean any software, application,
       extension, plugin, library, tool, service, script,
       publication, research output, dataset, model, or any
       other work — whether commercial, non-commercial,
       academic, or otherwise — that is based upon, derived
       from, adapted from, incorporates, or references any
       portion of the Software, including but not limited to
       modifications, translations, abridgements, extensions,
       integrations, functional reproductions, or any form
       in which the Software has been recast, transformed,
       or materially adapted.

  1.4  "Substantial Similarity" shall mean that fifty percent
       (50%) or more of the measurable lines of source code,
       logical structures, algorithmic constructs, functional
       components, or architectural patterns of a given work
       are identical to, functionally equivalent to, or
       discernibly derived from the Software, as assessed
       through objective code comparison methodologies or
       at the sole and reasonable determination of Defensive
       Grid Labs.

  1.5  "Licensee" shall mean any individual, legal entity,
       academic institution, research organization, government
       body, corporation, or automated system that accesses,
       utilizes, modifies, distributes, or references the
       Software in any capacity whatsoever.

  1.6  "Academic and Research Use" shall mean any use of the
       Software, in whole or in part, for purposes of
       scholarly research, academic study, scientific
       experimentation, publication in journals, conference
       proceedings, theses, dissertations, white papers,
       technical reports, presentations, or any other
       form of intellectual inquiry or educational output.

  1.7  "Contribution" shall mean any deliberate submission of
       source code, documentation, bug fixes, feature
       additions, or other materials to Defensive Grid Labs
       for incorporation into the Software.

  1.8  "Distribute" shall mean to make the Software or any
       Derivative Work available to any third party through
       any medium or channel, including but not limited to
       GitHub, npm, the Chrome Web Store, Firefox Add-ons
       Marketplace, app stores, package registries, websites,
       academic repositories, institutional repositories,
       preprint servers, or any private or commercial channel.

