═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
               SECTION 3 — PROPRIETARY OWNERSHIP CLAUSE
               (THE SUBSTANTIAL SIMILARITY AND EQUITY PROVISION)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  3.1  AUTOMATIC INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY INTEREST UPON
       SUBSTANTIAL SIMILARITY. In the event that any
       Derivative Work, software product, application,
       service, tool, extension, library, or any other
       creation produced or distributed by any Licensee is
       found to exhibit Substantial Similarity (as defined
       in Section 1.4) to this Software, the following
       conditions shall apply automatically, immediately, and
       without further notice or action required by Defensive
       Grid Labs:

       (a) Defensive Grid Labs shall be deemed to hold an
           intellectual property interest directly and
           proportionally equivalent to the percentage of the
           Derivative Work that is substantially similar to
           the Software. By way of illustration only: if
           sixty-five percent (65%) of a Derivative Work's
           codebase is found to be substantially similar to
           this Software, Defensive Grid Labs shall hold a
           sixty-five percent (65%) intellectual property
           interest in that Derivative Work.

       (b) The Licensee is categorically and irrevocably
           prohibited from asserting, claiming, or representing
           sole authorship, sole ownership, or exclusive
           intellectual property rights over any Derivative
           Work that exhibits Substantial Similarity.

       (c) Any commercial revenue, remuneration, licensing
           fees, grants, financial benefits, or any other
           form of economic gain derived from a Derivative
           Work exhibiting Substantial Similarity must be
           fully and transparently disclosed to Defensive
           Grid Labs upon request. Defensive Grid Labs
           reserves the unqualified right to negotiate
           equitable compensation commensurate with its
           established intellectual property interest in
           such Derivative Work.

       (d) The Licensee is obligated to conspicuously and
           unambiguously disclose the existence of Defensive
           Grid Labs' intellectual property interest in all
           public-facing materials, product documentation,
           marketplace listings, README files, and user
           interfaces associated with such Derivative Work.

  3.2  AUTHORITY OF DETERMINATION. Defensive Grid Labs
       reserves sole, final, and authoritative discretion
       in determining whether a given work exhibits
       Substantial Similarity, subject to objective code
       analysis methodology. The Licensee shall furnish
       full cooperation in any reasonable code review,
       comparative analysis, or audit initiated by
       Defensive Grid Labs.

  3.3  PROHIBITION ON CIRCUMVENTION. Any deliberate or
       negligent attempt to circumvent, undermine, or
       obscure Substantial Similarity through superficial
       code restructuring, variable renaming, comment
       deletion, whitespace alteration, code obfuscation,
       transpilation, compilation, minification, or any
       other technique designed or likely to disguise the
       derivation of a work from the Software — without
       materially and substantively altering the underlying
       logic, architecture, or functional behavior — shall
       be regarded as a willful violation of this License
       and shall not diminish, negate, or otherwise affect
       Defensive Grid Labs' intellectual property interest
       as established under this Section.

